# Omnifood Landing Page

A fully responsive landing page for **Omnifood**, a fictional AI-powered food delivery service. This front-end project was built to practice HTML, CSS (including Grid, Flexbox, and media queries), and vanilla JavaScript with real-world layout challenges and UX interactions.

## ğŸŒ Live Demo

https://github.com/tarik-thomas/Omnifood-Project

---

## ğŸ“„ Project Overview

The Omnifood landing page includes multiple interactive sections such as testimonials, pricing, a mobile-responsive nav menu, and a functional sign-up form layout. The layout adjusts fluidly across breakpoints from desktops to mobile devices.

### ğŸ§  Key Features

- Mobile-first responsive layout using CSS Grid & Flexbox
- Sticky navigation bar and smooth scrolling
- Mobile hamburger menu toggle with JavaScript
- Fully styled pricing and testimonial sections
- Reusable utility classes and clean BEM-style CSS
- Custom media queries for multiple breakpoints
- Form layout and placeholder design for user input

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Technologies Used

- HTML5 & Semantic Elements
- CSS3 (Grid, Flexbox, `clamp()`, custom properties)
- JavaScript (DOM manipulation, scroll effects, navigation toggling)
- Google Fonts: Rubik, Inter
- Ionicons (icon library)

